# Loading libraries

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.pipeline import make_pipeline
from sklearn.preprocessing import OrdinalEncoder, StandardScaler, LabelEncoder
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report
from sklearn.feature_selection import mutual_info_classif
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier

print("Loading libraries done!")

Loading libraries done!
In [126]:
# Loading dataset

train_dataset = pd.read_csv('train_dataset.csv').drop(['Unnamed: 0'], axis='columns')
test_dataset = pd.read_csv('test_dataset.csv').drop(['Unnamed: 0'], axis='columns')

X, y = train_dataset.drop(['Churn'], axis='columns'), train_dataset['Churn']
X_test, y_test = test_dataset.drop(['Churn'], axis='columns'), test_dataset['Churn']

print(f'X.shape {X.shape}; y.shape {y.shape}')
print(f'X_test.shape {X_test.shape}; y_test.shape {y_test.shape}')

X.shape (4788, 19); y.shape (4788,)
X_test.shape (1198, 19); y_test.shape (1198,)

Clustering¶

In [127]:
model = make_pipeline(
    OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value', unknown_value=-1),
    StandardScaler(),
    KMeans(n_clusters=2 ,n_jobs=-1)
)
model.fit(X)
model['kmeans'].labels_
Out[127]:
array([1, 0, 0, ..., 0, 0, 0], dtype=int32)
In [128]:
test_labels = model.predict(X_test)
test_labels
Out[128]:

In [129]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2, figsize=(15, 10))

sns.scatterplot(X_test['MonthlyCharges'], X_test['TotalCharges'], hue=test_labels, ax=ax[1])
fig.show()

Decison Trees¶

In [131]:
dt_model = make_pipeline(
    OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value', unknown_value=-1),
    StandardScaler(),
    DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=0)
)
dt_model
Out[131]:
Pipeline(steps=[('ordinalencoder',
                 OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value',
                                unknown_value=-1)),
                ('standardscaler', StandardScaler()),
                ('decisiontreeclassifier',
                 DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=0))])

Hyperparameter tuning with GridSearchCV¶

In [132]:
param_grid = {
    'decisiontreeclassifier__criterion': ['gini', 'entropy'],
    'decisiontreeclassifier__max_depth': [5, 7, 10, 12, 15, 17, 20],
    'decisiontreeclassifier__min_samples_split': [2, 3, 4],
    'decisiontreeclassifier__min_samples_leaf': [1, 2, 3]
}

best = GridSearchCV(dt_model, param_grid, n_jobs=-1)
best.fit(X, y)

print(f'Best model (CV score={best.best_score_})')
print(best.best_estimator_)

Best model (CV score=0.7652506637172968)
Pipeline(steps=[('ordinalencoder',
                 OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value',
                                unknown_value=-1)),
                ('standardscaler', StandardScaler()),
                ('decisiontreeclassifier',
                 DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=7, min_samples_leaf=3,
                                        random_state=0))])

Testing¶

In [133]:
y_pred = best.predict(X_test)
print(classification_report(y_true=y_test, y_pred=y_pred))

         Yes       0.50      0.59      0.54       315

    accuracy                           0.73      1198
   macro avg       0.67      0.69      0.68      1198

dt_model_cluster = make_pipeline(
    OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value', unknown_value=-1),
    StandardScaler(),
    DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=0)
)
dt_model_cluster
Out[136]:
Pipeline(steps=[('ordinalencoder',
                 OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value',
                                unknown_value=-1)),
                ('standardscaler', StandardScaler()),
                ('decisiontreeclassifier',
                 DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=0))])

Hyperparameter tuning with GridSearchCV¶

In [137]:
param_grid = {
    'decisiontreeclassifier__criterion': ['gini', 'entropy'],
    'decisiontreeclassifier__max_depth': [5, 7, 10, 12, 15, 17, 20],
    'decisiontreeclassifier__min_samples_split': [2, 3, 4],
    'decisiontreeclassifier__min_samples_leaf': [1, 2, 3]
}

best_cluster = GridSearchCV(dt_model_cluster, param_grid, n_jobs=-1)
best_cluster.fit(X, y)

print(f'Best model (CV score={best.best_score_})')
print(best.best_estimator_)

Best model (CV score=0.7652506637172968)
Pipeline(steps=[('ordinalencoder',
                 OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value',
                                unknown_value=-1)),
                ('standardscaler', StandardScaler()),
                ('decisiontreeclassifier',
                 DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=7, min_samples_leaf=3,
                                        random_state=0))])

Hyperparameter tuning with GridSearchCV¶

In [180]:
param_grid = {
    'decisiontreeclassifier__criterion': ['gini', 'entropy'],
    'decisiontreeclassifier__max_depth': [5, 7, 10, 12, 15, 17, 20],
    'decisiontreeclassifier__min_samples_split': [2, 3, 4],
    'decisiontreeclassifier__min_samples_leaf': [1, 2, 3]
}

best = GridSearchCV(dt_model_cluster, param_grid, n_jobs=-1)
best.fit(X[cols], y)

print(f'Best model (CV score={best.best_score_})')
print(best.best_estimator_)

Best model (CV score=0.7596095575290738)
Pipeline(steps=[('ordinalencoder',
                 OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value',
                                unknown_value=-1)),
                ('standardscaler', StandardScaler()),
                ('decisiontreeclassifier',
                 DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=5, random_state=0))])
